Text:
This a story from shortly after my lord rescued me
and took me to his home...
Yaaah!
Graaah!

Despite putting in everything I have, Delta manages
to counter, hitting me in the stomach with her
practice sword.
U-Ugh...
Unable able to scream, I writhe in pain.
Uh, that's enough.
Yeah! I win!

No, that wasn't good enough. Why did things have to
turn out this way...

With his hand over his face, my lord sighs in
disappointment.

I taught you to attack the upper body, right?
Gamma, your swings are too wide.
I saw an opening, so I went for it!

Delta, I told you not to strike because it's too
dangerous. If you're gonna be that way, it's
going to be impossible to teach you two
swordplay.
Ugh... I'll d-do it! I'll show you I can do it!

At this rate, my lord will cast me out. I don't want
to be an outcast anymore. I shall live up to his
expectations.

I guess we'll end today's training session. With how
sturdy Delta is, she should be okay.

I can be sturdy! For you, my lord, I am willing
to jump into any fire or cross any ocean!
I appreciate the thought.
I can see my lord smiling. Ah, how splendid!
I wish to repay my wonderful lord for taking me in.

Ow... This maiden's soft skin is like a blackened
banana...

As I check myself while taking a bath, I find my
body covered in bruises.

They’re so ugly, I’ll have to cover them in makeup
again... But when I sweat, it will just come off...

At least my lord acknowledged my strength,
but that's all...

Oh, Gamma. Did you just take a bath? You smell like
soap.
Yes, I just did.

My lord is very kind, strong, and handsome...
I want to be just like him.

But as I am right now, I'm getting hurt just trying
to keep up.

If this continues I'll only drag him down, and not
be able to repay him for taking me in.

To repay kindness with ingratitude is the worst
thing a person can do. Ah, I wonder if there's
any way to be useful to my lord.
I guess I'll take a bath too.
Well then, shall I wash your back?
Uh, well, didn't you just take a bath?

As long as you're taking one, my lord, I'll take as
many as I have to!
W-Well, I do appreciate that...

(Thanking me while politely declining... How
considerate! How wonderful he truly is!)
You don’t have to be so modest.

It’s like fried food, it gets better after frying it
another two or three times!

Well, taking a bath and cooking deep-fried food are
completely different things...

Then what should I do?! I'll do anything! Please,
tell me!
Hey, there’s no need for you to work so hard.
No, I have to!

(If I can't be of use to him in battle, then I must
find some other way...!)

(If I can't... If I can't, then there's no point of
me being in the Shadow Garden!)
Oh, by the way. Can you cook, Gamma?

Huh? Yes, I'm an average cook. But I'm not as good
as Epsilon.
Hmm, really...

(Does my lord's reaction indicate...that I have his
attention?!)

(I shall please my lord by cooking! I shall find my
way to his heart through his stomach!)
Cooking! What would you like to eat, my lord?!

Um...maybe curry would be nice. What do you
think, Gamma?
Curry...!

Duly noted! As unworthy as I am, I shall present you
with most ultimate, supremely delicious curry in
the world!

(Can I do it...? No, I have to do it. I shall prove
my worth by making the best curry ever!)
Alright, I shall begin cooking!
Huh? But I've already had dinner...

What are you saying?! It was you that taught me
Shadow Wisdom...
That curry! Tastes better! On the second day!
Y-You've learned well...

I heard you mention it once. At the time, I didn't
understand the meaning of this knowledge you
possess. Shadow Wisdom... I will absorb every
last word of your teachings!

I shall not rest until I have mastered this! Time to
get busy!

Curry... I shall make...curry. My lord!
...What is curry?!

Oh, right... I think we made it when we went
camping before, but I guess we just boiled it.
We didn't have any spices.

Spices...so in other words, curry is something you
boil with spices... Understood!

But when it comes to spices, there are many kinds of
them. Are you sure you understand...?
Of course, my lord!

Hehehe...I’m now one step closer to understanding
how to make curry!
A-Are sure you're up to it...?
